Resist the dark side of the force (dumb auto responders). Go to the light side and use smart automation that sounds and behaves just like you do.

DM the word “tour” if you want to sign up for the Futur Pro zoom tour Tuesday, Aug 17, 9am PDT.

Who can you trust? How to avoid fake gurus and what Mike Winnet calls “contrepreneurs”. They all follow a very specific formula to sell you a pipe dream—

You don’t need any special skill. You don’t need to posses any talent. Anybody can do it. It requires no money and little work and you can do it from anywhere by doing this one thing. Sigh.

Recently I was on the Millionaire Secrets podcast with @jefflernerofficial. We got into a fascinating and critical discussion as to why most creatives, designers (and entrepreneurs in general) will always struggle...
​​
​​...and never truly hit the big time. You can watch the full video on Jeff’s YouTube channel or on his podcast. Link in bio.

node.text:
For all the people in the back: a brand is not a logo. A brand isn’t what it looks like. The visual components are an important part of how customers experience a brand but it comes from something much deeper.

When properly managed, a brand can form an emotional connection with customers which creates preference. In order to do this, we must go deeper. Today’s guest post is by @dainwalker . Follow him for more useful tips like this.

I grew up in a time when there was no internet, no email and no social media. I remember having to ask my brother (who works in Silicon Valley) what is the internet?

People of my generation or older, are terrible with building a web presence. How do I know? I tried looking up some friends from school and they’re impossible to find.

What does this have to do with search? Everything. How hard are you making it for clients to find you? Try googling yourself without using your name or your company name. How did you do? Did you rank on the top 10 search results for _______?

This is why it’s so important to create content that’s valuable to your audience and aligned with your expertise.

Marketing, put simply, is the art of making it easier to find you than your competitor. Start with SEO. Get help from the SEO queen @itsjulekim .

But don’t stop there. Write. Produce video. Record a podcast. Make content. Do it until the world knows your name. This is how you get clients to come to you. Or, ignore this and chase clients for the rest of your life. Your choice.

Was this helpful? Make sure you follow my friend Jule for more tips on how to crush the SEO game.

What 3 words will people use to find you? For my service design agency, it was “brand strategy consultancy”. Give it a try. We should be ranked top 10.

Time is money. But not the way you think. The labor theory of value argues “that the economic value of a good or service is determined by the total amount of "socially necessary labor" required to produce it.”

Except in many cases, especially when time is critical, people will pay more to have something done quicker. Express flights, overnight delivery, 1 hour turn around all carry rush fees.

Charging hourly goes against this basic economic concept. I charging hourly, value is placed on how long something takes versus how effective the solution is. Stop selling time. Sell results.
